        "text": "Does JS 4.12 have a layout framework like the dijit.layout shown in this JS 3.29 example?\n\nhttps://developers.arcgis.com/javascript/3/jssamples/layout_fullmaplayoutwithborderandmargin.html\n\nGregory,\n\nHere is the 4.x version of that sample.\n\n<!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head> <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"> <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1,user-scalable=no\" /> <title>Full Map Layout - Border and Margin</title> <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://js.arcgis.com/4.12/dijit/themes/claro/claro.css\" /> <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://js.arcgis.com/4.12/esri/themes/light/main.css\" /> <style> html, body { height: 100%; width: 100%; margin: 0; padding: 0; } body { background-color: #feffff; overflow: hidden; font-family: \"Trebuchet MS\"; margin: 2%; } #viewDiv { -moz-border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; border: solid 4px #799d15; } </style> <script> var dojoConfig = { parseOnLoad: true }; </script> <script src=\"https://js.arcgis.com/4.12/\"></script> <script> require([ \"esri/Map\", \"esri/views/MapView\", \"dijit/layout/BorderContainer\", \"dijit/layout/ContentPane\" ], function(Map, MapView) { var map = new Map({ basemap: \"streets\" }); var view = new MapView({ container: \"viewDiv\", map: map, zoom: 4, center: [-102.524, 46.937] }); }); </script> </head> <body class=\"claro\"> <div data-dojo-type=\"dijit/layout/BorderContainer\" data-dojo-props=\"design:'headline', gutters:false\" style=\"width: 96%; height: 94%;\"> <div id=\"viewDiv\" data-dojo-type=\"dijit/layout/ContentPane\" data-dojo-props=\"region:'center'\"> </div> </div> </body> </html> ‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍‍"
